headline: Lululemon earnings, Fed commentary, housing data: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime hosts Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton outline what to watch on Thursday, March 27. Winnebago Industries (WGO) will report earnings in the morning, and Lululemon (LULU) will announce fourth quarter results after the bell. Federal Reserve Bank of Boston president Susan Collins and Federal Reserve Bank of Richmond president Tom Barkin will be speaking in the afternoon. Pending home sales data for February will be released in the morning, with economists expecting an increase of 1%. Freddie Mac mortgage rate data will be released in the afternoon. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.
